'''Harry Lee Poe''' is the [[Charles Colson]] Chair of Faith and Culture at [[Union University]] in [[Jackson, Tennessee]], and author of a number of books.

He is an indirect descendant of the family of [[Edgar Allan Poe]]<ref name="dc2003">{{cite news | publisher = [[The Daily Courier (Arizona)|The Daily Courier]] | date = January 20, 2003 | title = No one disturbs graceful mystery of Poe visitor }}</ref> and president of the [[Poe Foundation]].<ref>{{cite news | publisher = [[Washington Post]] | title = A Paean to Poe | date = January 15, 2006 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.poemuseum.org/about-staff.php | title = Staff | work = Poe Museum | accessdate = 2010-10-09 }}</ref> He was the director of the Poe writers conference in 2007.<ref>[http://www.poemuseum.org/news_and_events/writers_conference2007.html Edgar Allan Poe Young Writer’s Conference]</ref>

His book "Edgar Allan Poe: An Illustrated Companion to His Tell-Tale Stories" won the Edgar Award for 2009 in the category best critical/biographical. The same book received an Agatha nomination for best non-fiction book.<ref>[http://www.uu.edu/scholarship/employee.cfm?emp=hpoe]</ref>

